{"parse":{"title":"International Terrestrial Reference Frame (ITRF)","pageid":2802,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><span class=\"mw-lingo-term\" data-lingo-term-id=\"7fc56270e7a70fa81a5935b72eacbe29\">A</span> realisation of the International Terrestrial Reference System (ITRS) - a world spatial reference system with its origin at the centre of the Earth. Numbers following the designation ITRF specify the last year from which data was used in the datum definition e.<span class=\"mw-lingo-term\" data-lingo-term-id=\"b2f5ff47436671b6e533d8dc3614845d\">g</span>. ITRF 97. <span class=\"mw-lingo-term\" data-lingo-term-id=\"7fc56270e7a70fa81a5935b72eacbe29\">A</span> <span class=\"mw-lingo-term\" data-lingo-term-id=\"d6f7806b5d17e3c6493a6578ab64fd5a\">GNSS</span> or other radio-navigation system may be referenced to a specific ITRF designation so that it can be precisely related to the physical world.\n</p><p><br>\nSource: Nick Ward, Vicechair, <span class=\"mw-lingo-term\" data-lingo-term-id=\"0a1217bfe27a54fc7e55b72fc62c2371\">IALA</span> e-Nav Committee, March 2009\n</p>\n<div class=\"LanguageLinks\">\n<table width=\"100%\">\n<tbody><tr valign=\"top\" style=\"background: #FFFFFF\">\n<td style=\"width: 25px; padding-left: 0em; border-right: 1px solid #aaaaaa;border-left: 1px solid #EEF3E2;border-top: 1px solid #EEF3E2;border-bottom: 1px solid #EEF3E2;\"><span typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"/wiki/dictionary/index.php/File:25px-Geographylogo.png\" class=\"mw-file-description\" title=\"Languages\"><img alt=\"Languages\" src=\"/wiki/dictionary/images/8/82/25px-Geographylogo.png\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"25\" height=\"25\" class=\"mw-file-element\"></a></span></td>\n<td style=\"padding: 1px 1em 0; background: #EEF3E2;\">\n<p><b><a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">English</a></b>\n<span></span>\n<span></span>\n<span></span>\n<span></span>\n</p>\n</td></tr></tbody></table></div></div><div class=\"mw-lingo-tooltip\" id=\"7fc56270e7a70fa81a5935b72eacbe29\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition navigation-not-searchable\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition-text\">\n<p>ampere\n</p>\n</div></div>\n</div><div class=\"mw-lingo-tooltip\" id=\"b2f5ff47436671b6e533d8dc3614845d\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition navigation-not-searchable\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition-text\">\n<p>acceleration due to gravity (m/s2)\n</p>\n</div></div>\n</div><div class=\"mw-lingo-tooltip\" id=\"d6f7806b5d17e3c6493a6578ab64fd5a\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition navigation-not-searchable\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition-text\">\n<p>Global Navigation Satellite System\n</p>\n</div></div>\n</div><div class=\"mw-lingo-tooltip\" id=\"0a1217bfe27a54fc7e55b72fc62c2371\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition navigation-not-searchable\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition-text\">\n<p>International Association of Marine Aids to Navigation and Lighthouse Authorities - AISM\n</p>\n</div></div>\n</div>\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260615172757\nCache expiry: 86400\nReduced expiry: false\nComplications: []\nCPU time usage: 0.031 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.039 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 58/1000000\nPost\u2010expand include size: 823/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 632/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 7/100\nExpensive parser function count: 4/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post\u2010expand size: 0/5000000 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%   12.217      1 Template:Languages\n100.00%   12.217      1 -total\n 61.47%    7.510      4 Template:Languages/Lang\n-->\n\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key wiki_iala_dictionary_1_41:pcache:idhash:2802-0!canonical and timestamp 20260615172757 and revision id 9651. Rendering was triggered because: page-view\n -->\n</div>"},"langlinks":[],"categories":[{"sortkey":"","*":"10.1_General_e-Navigation_terms"},{"sortkey":"","*":"Alphabetical_Index"},{"sortkey":"","*":"IALA_Dictionary_2009_Edition"},{"sortkey":"